parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rust and corrosion of the frame can cause the vehicle to break apart while driving, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Clunking sounds coming from under the vehicle
fuel tank and fuel lines rusting out
and the vehicle becoming unsafe to drive.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Line Failure due to Rust
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lines can cause the loss of brakes, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: and the vehicle becoming unsafe to drive.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rusting and failure of brake lines can cause a loss of brake fluid, leading to a complete loss of braking ability, which can result in accidents and injuries.
symptoms: pulling or jerking when applying the brakes

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rusting of the frame and suspension components can compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle, leading to safety risks and potential accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake System Failure and Premature Wear
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of brake system components, including brake pads, shoes, and master cylinders, can cause a loss of braking ability, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Premature wear of front brake pads
anti-lock brake light lamp coming on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of electrical system components, such as wire harnesses, can cause malfunctions, including fuel pump failure, which can lead to safety risks and accidents.
symptoms: Wire harness burning under the seat

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Head gasket failure can cause engine damage, stalling, and loss of power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. It can also lead to costly repairs and potentially cause damage to other engine components.
Engine stalling can cause loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded, especially when driving at high speeds.
Catalytic converter issues can cause noise, vibration, and potentially lead to engine damage or failure.
